RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Louisiana Bred NW2 $5000 & NW3 $5000 Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOUIS LE GRANDE broke out at the start, chased along the inside, was roused to secure position inside of rivals entering the turn, progressed to gain place from an outer rival at the quarter pole, drifted outwardly many paths through upper stretch while pursuing the clear leader, then ranged up to that foe at the furlong grounds, drove past entering the final sixteenth, and drew clear. BLUSHINSTREETDEVIL cleared off and crossed over at the half mile pole, showed the way in hand around the turn, was shaken up after the rider looked for challenges leaving the quarter pole, came under a drive in midstretch as an outer rival menaced, but offered little resistance at the sixteenth pole, gave way, and narrowly saved place. SEMI CHARMED LIFE got keen before shifting outside of the clearing leader at the half mile pole, stalked two wide, but lost place to an inner rival entering the lane, got floated outwardly many paths through upper stretch while sustaining a chase, failed to match rallying stride entering the final furlong, then kept on in the late stages, but missed reached place. COURAGEOUS TIMMY broke a step slow and took back from tight quarters between horses at the start, raced at the rear along the inside, improved entering the lane, and failed to threaten the top trio. PLEASANT VISION lacked speed four wide, and made little impact. ROOSTER RUN leaned inwardly at the start, pursued from midpack three wide and between horses, and faded.

HUMOR ME PLEASE pursued the leader from between a pair of rivals into the first turn, rated back and shifted out to the four path exiting that bend, shifted three to four wide entering the lane, and stayed on while hanging on his left lead. LIMA ZULU set the pace inside of a vying rival, then inside of a pair of foes into the far turn as MOTOWN MISSLE joined the fray, but proved no match for that one turning for home, sustained place through midstretch, but lost that position at the sixteenth pole. G'S LAW bobbled a bit leaving the gates, raced at the rear along the inside, vacated the rail to surpass a tiring rival turning for home, and failed to factor. LA BOUCANE vied for the lead two wide, then from between horses around the far turn, but proved no match for his outer counterpart turning for home, then weakened in upper stretch while resisting a lead change. WINNING DANCE tracked along the inside, chased the top trio around the far turn, but weakened turning for home.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (For Horses That Sold Or Rna For $50,000 Or Less In Their Most Recent Auction).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WORK ORDER pressed two wide and between horses, vied turning for home, led in the three path entering the lane, shifted down to the two path leaving the quarter pole to shut the door on JULIA'S WARRIOR's bid attempt, then drove clear nearing midstretch, and inched away. JULIA'S WARRIOR took a bump from an inner rival soon after the start, tracked the top flight from the two to three paths around the turn, inched closer to be just behind them entering the lane, but put an inner rival to tight quarters while attempting to gain position inside of the leader leaving the quarter pole, lacked the needed kick to bid through a rail opening in upper stretch, chased the clearing leader into the final furlong, and secured place at the sixteenth pole while hanging on his left lead. BOOSTER SHOT bumped an outer rival leaving the gates, chased four wide, yielded to inner foes in the five path entering the lane, drifted to the seven path approaching midstretch, yet kept on in the final furlong to gain show late. RATE CONFIRMATION stalked three wide, bid turning for home, but yielded in the four path while hanging on his left lead in upper stretch, sustained a chase while changing over at the three sixteenths pole, but tired in closing stages. POWER ALLEY was slow early, trailed along the inside, shifted to the five path in upper stretch, stayed on mildly between horses, and missed reaching show. GEM COLLECTION broke out at the start, set the pace inside of a pair of pressing foes around the turn, but was headed turning for home, checked when put to tight rail quarters leaving the quarter pole, and weakened. THE TRAINER OF GEM COLLECTION CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF JULIA'S WARRIOR FOR INTERFERENCE IN UPPER STRETCH; BUT THE OBJECTION WAS DISALLOWED BY THE STEWARDS.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LORDY LORDY was fractious in the post parade, pressed the leader from the outside, required urging to sustain pressure in the three path and between horses around the turn, vied in the five path entering the lane, drifted out to the eight path in upper stretch, sustained a duel through the final sixteenth, and narrowly prevailed. CUSTOM CADILLAC set the pace in the two path, shifted out to the five path in upper stretch while maintaining a margin from an outer rival, showed the way into the final furlong while hanging on his left lead, dueled through the final sixteenth, and got nailed at the wire. BOSTON BLITZ broke inwardly, bumped the inner part of the gate before bumping and bothering an inner rival at the start, chased two wide and between horses while under steady urging, vied for show between horses in midstretch, and edged that position through the final sixteenth. IRON MOON was bumped and bothered by an outer rival at the start, stalked along the inside, but only managed to chase in upper stretch before fading. THROWIN' SHADE tracked three wide while in the four path around the turn, fanned to the six path entering the lane, and gave way while hanging on his left lead. LONE STAR MAX veered out at the start, and got outrun.

MR. FOUR SEVENS vied for the lead inside of the eventual winner, but was headed by that wide foe around the far turn, fought on through midstretch, but yielded in the late stages, yet held place. HUDSON'S TURN bobbled at the start, rated at the rear two wide, inched closer in the five path around the far turn, but leveled off in midstretch, vied for show between horses in the closing stages, and dead-heated for that position. SILVER GALAXY pursued from midpack two wide, then from the four path and among rivals around the far turn, sustained a chase between foes through midstretch, then emerged late to dead heat for show. OH MY ACHING ARCH saved ground towards the rear, then lacked the needed rail kick. REAL CITY SPEED tracked three wide, pursued from the five path around the far turn, fanned to the eight path entering the lane, drifted to the ten path in upper stretch, chased the top pair while one-paced through midstretch, and yielded to inner rivals late. MOMENT OF STARDOM saved ground in midpack, tipped out in upper stretch, chased between horses in the final furlong, and yielded late. APACHE TEARS prompted the pace three wide, stalked the top pair entering the backstretch, but weakened in hand between horses turning for home.
